{
  "texts": [
    "This strategic move aimed to position the dataset in competition with, or even as a potential successor to, established datasets like KITTI (Geiger et al. 2012) or nuScenes (Caesar et al. 2020), known for their significance in advancing machine vision research.",
    "For participants, the allure was also related to the prospect of applying their burgeoning machine vision skills, a significant number of whom were either computer science PhD students or recent graduates.",
    "The challenges provided a unique avenue to not only exercise their newly acquired general skills on well-defined (machine vision) problems within real-world contexts but also to engage with trendy or cutting-edge domains such as autonomous driving.",
    "By affording participants the opportunity to channel their expertise in such a way, Waymo harnessed the synergy between emergent skills and pertinent application.",
    "The Waymo challenges granted participants access to sensor data and computational resources that would otherwise be unreachable or unfeasible, inaccessible to most researchers unless affiliated with esteemed institutions like CMU or Stanford."
  ]
}